variables.name: POWER_USAGE_LOW

variables.comment: * A constant indicating a medium power usage.

variables.name: ACCURACY_FINE
variables.comment: * A constant indicating a finer location accuracy.

methods.name: public boolean hasNetworkRequirement()
methods.comment: * True if provider requires access to a data network (e.g., the Internet).

methods.name: public boolean hasSatelliteRequirement()
methods.comment: * True if the provider requires access to a satellite-based positioning system (e.g., GPS).

methods.name: public boolean hasCellRequirement()
methods.comment: * True if the provider requires access to a cellular network (e.g., for cell tower IDs).

methods.name: public boolean hasMonetaryCost()
methods.comment:
* True if this provider may result in a monetary charge to the user. Network usage is not
     * considered a monetary cost.

methods.name: public boolean hasAltitudeSupport()
methods.comment: * True if the provider is able to provide altitude under at least some conditions.

methods.name: public boolean hasSpeedSupport()
methods.comment: * True if the provider is able to provide speed under at least some conditions.

methods.name: public boolean hasBearingSupport()
methods.comment: * True if the provider is able to provide bearing under at least some conditions.

methods.name: public int getAccuracy()
methods.comment:
* Rough location accuracy for this provider, primarily with respect to horizontal location
     * accuracy.
